$\mathbf{a}=\left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{3},\frac{1}{3},\frac{1}{3}\right)$
\end{minipage}.Once we know the position vector of the circumcenter, we notice that that point does not change during the extension of line segment $\overrightarrow{AP}$.As the line segment $\overrightarrow{AP}$ extends in both directions, to make it symmetrical, we know that $Q$ is the point which lies in the plane $BCD$ and which has the distance of $AP$ from $A$ with opposite sign in the direction of line segment $\overrightarrow{AP}$. Now $OQ = |OP|$, the desired ratio is $OP/AO/1/3$ <the answer>1/3 </answer>

